title: WebSocket Chat with Presence

participant Alice Browser as A
participant WebSocket Server as WS
participant Redis PubSub as Redis
participant Bob Browser as B

A->>WS: WS Connect /chat?token=xxx
note over WS: Validate token, register connection
WS->>Redis: SADD online_users "alice"
WS->>Redis: PUBLISH presence { alice: online }
Redis-->>B: presence: alice is online
WS-->>A: Connected { room: "general" }
note over A: Alice types a message
A->>WS: { type: "message", text: "Hey Bob!" }
WS->>WS: Validate & sanitize
WS->>Redis: PUBLISH chat:general { from: alice }
note over WS: Persist to message store
Redis-->>B: chat message from alice
WS-->>A: { type: "ack", msgId: "msg_301" }
B->>WS: { type: "typing", room: "general" }
WS->>Redis: PUBLISH typing { user: bob }
Redis-->>A: bob is typing...
B->>WS: { type: "message", text: "Hi Alice!" }
WS->>Redis: PUBLISH chat:general { from: bob }
Redis-->>A: chat message from bob
note over A: Alice closes tab
A-->WS: Connection closed
WS->>Redis: SREM online_users "alice"
WS->>Redis: PUBLISH presence { alice: offline }
Redis-->>B: presence: alice is offline
